
[1]baccifferous

   BACCIF'FEROUS, a.[L.baccifer,of bacca, a berry, and fero, to bear.]

   That produces berries. [See Bacca.] Bacciferous plants formerly
   included all such plants as have a pulpy fruit, whether of the apple,
   berry or cherry kind; but the modern systems of botany comprehend under
   this description such plants only as bear the pulpy pericarp, called
   bacca, or berry.
